					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12090689#post-4286522</guid>
				<title>+1</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12090689/scp-4841#post-4286522</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Thu, 20 Jun 2019 14:32:42 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>DrSevere</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>511038</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Very good, sufficiently weird, I don't fully get it but that's okay.</p> <p>Couple minor nitpicks:</p> <blockquote> <p>Foundation archeological digs are planned in the vicinity of SCP-4841 for mid-2020.</p> </blockquote> <p>Might wanna move that date back or just make it &quot;near future&quot; or something, unless you're planning to update this next year.</p> <blockquote> <p>Any depiction of a human figure brought into SCP-4841 will, after an indeterminate period of time beneath one hour, begin to anomalously generate blood around the eyes and wrists in the painting</p> </blockquote> <p>It says &quot;Depiction&quot; but then only talks about paintings afterwards. What about statues, photographs, etc?</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
